### Executive Summary  
ABM Industries has delivered a decisive upward revision to its Q4 and full-year guidance, underpinned by a robust Q3 performance that materially exceeded consensus expectations. Revenue grew 10.7% year-over-year to $1.54 billion, while adjusted EPS of $0.90 beat estimates by a wide margin, signaling strong near-term operational momentum. Despite a reported GAAP loss per share of $0.20 from continuing operations—which introduces earnings quality concerns—the company’s raised outlook and management’s confident tone support a bullish near-to-medium-term stance.

